    "body": "### Problem\n\nAs the title says, `vim.ui.open(\"https://www.neovim.org\")` works on stable but not on nightly. They appear to both be returning the same thing,\n\n**nightly**\n```\n{\n  _state = {\n    cmd = <1>{ \"cmd.exe\", \"/c\", \"start\", \"\", \"https://www.neovim.io\" },\n    done = false,\n    handle = <userdata 1>,\n    pid = 14352,\n    stderr = <userdata 2>,\n    stderr_data = {},\n    stdout = <userdata 3>,\n    stdout_data = {}\n  },\n  cmd = <table 1>,\n  pid = 14352,\n  <metatable> = {\n    __index = {\n      _timeout = <function 1>,\n      is_closing = <function 2>,\n      kill = <function 3>,\n      wait = <function 4>,\n      write = <function 5>\n    }\n  }\n}\nnil\n```\n\n**stable**\n```\n{\n  _state = {\n    cmd = <1>{ \"cmd.exe\", \"/c\", \"start\", \"\", \"https://www.neovim.io\" },\n    done = false,\n    handle = <userdata 1>,\n    pid = 19804,\n    stderr = <userdata 2>,\n    stderr_data = {},\n    stdout = <userdata 3>,\n    stdout_data = {}\n  },\n  cmd = <table 1>,\n  pid = 19804,\n  <metatable> = {\n    __index = {\n      _timeout = <function 1>,\n      is_closing = <function 2>,\n      kill = <function 3>,\n      wait = <function 4>,\n      write = <function 5>\n    }\n  }\n}\nnil\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Run `:lua vim.ui.open(\"https://www.neovim.org\")`\n2. Does not open in browser\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTo open the link in the browser like in stable\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-404+g7fff439395\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWIndows Terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nN/A\n\n### Installation\n\nbob",
